   =20
      NFT Stuff
   =20
 =20

If I had told you, in 2021, that some combination=C2=A0of (1) putting laser=
 eyes on your Twitter profile picture and (2) then replacing your Twitter p=
rofile picture with a picture of a Bored Ape might cause you to go blind, y=
ou would have said things like =E2=80=9Cwhat=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cno, you =
don=E2=80=99t understand, Twitter profile pictures are not real life, putti=
ng lasers in the eyes of your picture does not cause actual lasers to beam =
into your physical eyes and render you blind, this is a very elementary mis=
take.=E2=80=9D But you would have been wrong.  Here is a thing:

Several people have reported experiencing eye pain, vision problems, and su=
nburnt skin on Sunday after attending ApeFest, a Bored Ape Yacht Club NFT c=
ollection event in Hong Kong that ran from November 3rd-5th.
Some ApeFest attendees posted on X (formerly Twitter) after seeking medical=
 attention, with one person reporting that they had been diagnosed with Pho=
tokeratitis =E2=80=94 aka, =E2=80=9Cwelder=E2=80=99s eye,=E2=80=9D a condit=
ion caused by unprotected exposure to ultraviolet radiation =E2=80=94 and a=
nother saying the issue was a result of UV from the stage lights, leading t=
o speculation that the injuries were caused by improper lighting used at th=
e event.

Albert Burneko  writes:
This is the sort of thing that happens to Homer Simpson. It happens to Mast=
er Shake. If you were reading a satirical novel and it mentioned a bunch of=
 fanatical HODLers going blind at a festival for their dead worthless Ponzi=
-tech garbage because they stood there like passive dullards and stared int=
o a fly-by-night lasertag lighting array equivalent to the sun while variou=
s sweaty Shingy-type guys ideated at them, you would snort-laugh and kinda =
roll your eyes and go, "Oh, come on."
I guess next month there will be a story=C2=A0about non-fungible token coll=
ectors at ApeFest  drinking slurp juice and transforming into mutant monkey=
s? Is it possible that the world is a simulation, and that crypto is someho=
w the nexus between the simulated world we experience and the computer that=
 runs it? If your Bored Ape dies, do you die in real life? Are NFTs=C2=A0ma=
gic? Probably not, no, probably someone just messed up the lighting at ApeF=
est. Still, bizarre.

